      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "rationale": "Software quality assurance was reviewed. Version control and issue tracking are in place, but formal V&V plan documentation and independent code review are absent. Achieved level falls short of the required level for MRL 5.",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "At MRL 5, SQA must demonstrate a fully documented V&V plan, independent code review, and traceable change control. Required level 4 reflects the need for systematic SQA processes commensurate with Class III device risk."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "rationale": "Code verification activities were limited to basic benchmarks. No formal method of manufactured solutions (MMS) study was conducted. The achieved level of 2 does not satisfy the required level 4 for this MRL.",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Required level 4 is set because MRL 5 demands rigorous numerical code verification including MMS or equivalent formal methods to bound discretization and implementation errors. This threshold is consistent with FDA guidance for primary-evidence CFD submissions."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "rationale": "A mesh refinement study was conducted at a single operating point only. Grid convergence index (GCI) was not computed across all five operating conditions. Achieved level is 2.",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Required level 4 mandates a systematic GCI study across all operating conditions with demonstrated asymptotic convergence. The threshold is set at 4 for MRL 5 because discretization error directly propagates into hemolysis index predictions used as primary regulatory evidence."
    },
