      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "rationale": "Experimental test conditions partially matched the COU operating envelope. Blood analog fluid properties were used rather than ovine or human blood. Some boundary conditions deviate from clinical VAD operating ranges."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "rationale": "Output comparison was performed qualitatively. Quantitative error metrics and uncertainty bounds on the comparison were not reported for all operating points. Achieved level is 2 against a required level of 4."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "rationale": "The hemolysis index is the primary QoI. Validation data includes hemolysis measurements, but secondary QoIs such as shear stress distributions and residence time were not directly validated.",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Required level 3 is established because the hemolysis QoI is the direct regulatory endpoint; validation must demonstrate that the model captures the physical mechanisms governing hemolysis, not merely aggregate output agreement."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "rationale": "Validation activities were conducted on the FDA generic pump geometry, which approximates but does not replicate the specific VAD device geometry. Operating conditions in validation tests covered 3 of 5 required COU operating points.",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Required level 4 reflects that for a Class III VAD submission, validation activities must be conducted under conditions that closely replicate the COU geometry and full operating envelope. Extrapolation beyond validated conditions is not acceptable at MRL 5."
    },
